CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 27, 1956, pg. 3, reads: "'Hole in Shoe' - Students of Fifth Ave. High School volunteered to march through the downtown section on Oct. 23 in the 'Walk With Adlai' drive and shine shoes without any pay. Placard shown on right is reminder of Stevenson's 1952 'hole in my shoe.' ... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Three young women shining shoes of three men, in booth with sign inscribed "Free Shines by Volunteers for Stevenson," for Adlai Stevenson campaign
